Please don't feel like you didn't have a productive morning just because all you did was edit :) I feel like people don't take in the time a task takes them into their productivity. You can have done multiple small tasks in a day and feel like you were being productive, but if they were all pretty small and you didn't do the longer tasks that are actually important, you weren't actually that productive. That's why I always make a priority list in my to do list so I can make sure I actually do the things I need to do, instead of doing a lot of small things that don't matter as much. You finishing your edit is probably your priority task (especially since you can't really go anywhere) you had a very productive morning, ready for the rest of the day :) Ofcourse you have days where you don't have to do as much, but I find making a priority list with the top 3 things to do a very good way of keeping track of what I HAVE to do versus what I would WANT to do for fun.
